pread notion that wealth and generosity go hand in hand. In a thoughtful and balanced conclusion, the author explores the cost of our longstanding attitudes toward the rich. Among the case studies in America's Good Rich:Puritan merchant Robert KeayneGeorge WashingtonManufacturers Amos & Abbot LawrenceOil magnate John D. RockefellerBill GatesWarren BuffetSteve JobsOprah Winfrey  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCharitieszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aDemocracyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aEqualityzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRich people -- United States -- History. 0aRich peoplezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWealth -- United States -- History. 0aWealthzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Philanthropy & Charity.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018888240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300188882423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300188882/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles